      "content": "While many successful democracies do rely on national identity to maintain social cohesion, this does not mean national pride is inherently bad for democracy. In fact, a strong national identity can be a necessary foundation for a functioning democracy, as it provides the shared values and collective purpose that allow citizens to engage in democratic processes. The danger arises not from the existence of national identity itself, but from how it is manipulated to justify authoritarianism, suppress dissent, or exclude marginalized groups from the benefits of the state.",
